Mr Chebukati stressed that the publication of names of persons contesting in party primaries and those intending to contest as independent candidates is not “clearance of candidates to contest in an election.” The electoral commission is set to gazette at least 18 names of persons who have expressed interest in the Nairobi gubernatorial race.
The list, according to impeccable sources at the Independent Electoral and Boundaries Commission (IEBC), has 13 independent aspirants -- including former Kiambu Governor Ferdinand Waititu -- and five hopefuls from the Jubilee party.



