In his ruling, Justice Anthony Mrima temporarily stopped the mini poll on the basis of Mr Sonko’s petition challenging the process that led to his ouster late last year. Feeling cornered after being charged with the theft of Sh357 million, Governor Mike Sonko went on the rampage. He is seeking to stop the Nairobi by-election and the vetting of deputy governor nominee, Anne Kananu Mwenda. Majimbo Simiyu Kalasinga bagged the Ford Kenya party ticket by beating Nakuru East Sub-county Commissioner Erick Wanyonyi 75 to 30 votes. Senate Majority Chief Whip says he did not give the letter to any media outlet.